    "/assets/search": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Search Assets",
        "description": "<p>Filters assets by a given set of parameters and returns the filtered assets as well as the total number of assets in the filtered set. By default, only active assets with open vulnerabilities are returned.</p><p>Each unique parameter is combined using AND while each of values passed in a single array will be combined using OR. For example, if you search for all assets with <code>status[]=[\"active\"]</code> and <code>tags[]=[\"foo\", \"bar\"]</code> you will receive all active assets that have either a \"foo\" tag or a \"bar\" tag. </p><p><table>  <tr>    <th>Attribute</th>    <th>Value</th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Maximum Pages Allowed</td>    <td>20</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Maximum Page Size</td>    <td>50,000</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Default Page Size</td>    <td>500</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Total Count Present in <code>meta</code> object</td>    <td>Yes</td>  </tr></table>Large page size can cause performance issues.  See the <a href=\"https://apidocs.kennasecurity.com/reference/pagination\">Pagination Section</a> for more details. </p><p>This endpoint does not return tag source information. Tag source information is available in the <a href=\"https://apidocs.kennasecurity.com/reference/list-tags\">List Tags</a> endpoint.<p>",
        "operationId": "search-assets",
        "security": [
          {
            "X-Risk-Token": [

            ]
          }
        ],
        "tags": [
          "ASSETS"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "application_id",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The ID of an application to retrieve assets for. All other search parameters are ignored if application_id is provided.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "exclude_child_filter[]",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "description": "If you want to include all assets regardless of vulnerability filters, pass a value of [\"Include all assets\"]; otherwise, omit this parameter."
          },
          {
            "name": "id[]",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            },
            "description": "Array of asset IDs"
          },
          {
            "name": "max_priority",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Search for all assets that have a priority less than this value.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "min_priority",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Search for all assets that have a priority greater than this value.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "max_risk_meter_score",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Search for all assets that have a risk meter score less than this value.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "min_risk_meter_score",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Search for all assets that have a risk meter score greater than this value.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "page",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The page number from 1 to 20.",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "per_page",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The page size from 1 to 50,000.  Default page size is 500. A page size of 5,000 is recommended.  Larger page sizes can cause performance issues.",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "operating_system[]",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "description": "An array of the names of the operating systems associated with a set of assets."
          },
          {
            "name": "primary_locator[]",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "description": "The primary locator used for an asset. This should be one of the following values: ip_address, hostname, database, url, mac_address, netbios, fqdn, file, or application"
          },
          {
            "name": "q",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Additional text search parameters, as documented at: [Kenna Search Terms](https://help.kennasecurity.com/hc/en-us/articles/206280593-Kenna-Search-Terms), section \"Asset Terms\".  Example q=tag:(mytag+AND+thetag).",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "service_names[]",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "description": "An array of service names relating to your assets. Make sure all letters are lowercase."
