        "description": "<p>Get all results from a previously created asynchronous search using the search_id.</p><p>The response is gzipped and the content of the response data is determined by the <code>model</code> field in <code>export_settings</code> in the <a href=\"https://apidocs.kennasecurity.com/reference/request-data-export\">Request Data Export API's</a> body parameters.  Usually, the response is stored in a file and ungzipped.</p><p>If your search has not been completed you will receive an Export Incomplete Response to indicate that we are still processing your search results.</p><p>The response example shows an ungzipped response for asset exports; whereas, the response schema shows the options of returning asset, fix, or vulnerability information in an ungzipped format.</p><p>For more details, refer to <a href=\"https://apidocs.kennasecurity.com/reference/downloading-export-files\">Downloading Export Files<a>.</p>",
